<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-08T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="82" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.34/172: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-08T16:00:00-04:00">July 8,
                                    1935—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>169. Your 304, July 8, 5 p.m. A telegram dated July 5 from our Embassy at
                                Berlin<note n="31" xml:id="d82fn31">Telegram No. 132, not
                                printed.</note> requested that we inform the Navy Department that
                            the Assistant Naval Attaché was mailing the German construction program
                            “communicated, in strict confidence to Washington Treaty Powers”. The
                            telegram then lists the numbers, tonnage and gun calibre of vessels
                            under construction or to be laid down in 1935. This is the only
                            information we have received on the subject from Germany or any other
                            country.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>